"""Snakemake workflow: zero-shot VEP scoring experiment.

Train-split only. 5 models × 3 datasets × 3 windows = 45 (model, window, dataset)
score parquets, each yielding 30 score columns × 8 subsets + 2 global aggregations.

Stage 1 (GPU): extract_features — 4-pass forward + on-the-fly scoring → small
    per-variant parquet (no embedding cache; scores computed in-batch).
Stage 2 (CPU): compute_metrics — pairwise accuracy + binomial-test p-value per
    subset + global pooled + macro (t-test p-value for macro).
Stage 3 (CPU): aggregate_metrics — concat into a single parquet + csv for the
    tracking issue body.
"""


